        "text": ". Though the writer of Chronicles has not in this description mentioned any chains as appertaining to the oracle, yet they are mentioned in the parallel. The selection of what is said has in our present text so much the appearance of haste, that this may account for the abrupt appearance of the allusion here. Otherwise the words, \"in the oracle,\" tempt us to fear some corruptness of text, scarcely safely removed by Bertheau's suggestion to substitute ",
